OL,6,FProfessor Dee Boersma is, by her own
OL,7,Fadmission, "madly in love" with
OL,8,Fpenguins. She has spent half a century
OL,9,Ftravelling to the ends of the Earth to
OL,10,Fstudy, tag and monitor the flightless
OL,11,Fbird in the hope of preserving it.
OL,13,FThe academic recently returned from
OL,14,FPunta Tombo in Argentina on her annual
OL,15,Fvisit for a project she began in 1982
OL,16,Fstudying the Magellanic penguin. And
OL,17,Fthis year she will visit the Galapagos
OL,18,Fislands to continue a programme
OL,19,Fencouraging the breeding of the
OL,20,FGalapagos penguin which began when she
OL,21,Fwas still a graduate student.
OL,3,C70% of penguin marriages end in
OL,4,C'divorce', says leading academic
